race.comment: Another very even race with little between the top chances but going with the leaders. SUZE SPRITZ (11) is an honest type who was a winner two back this journey then placed over a little further last time, beaten just over a length. Has a low draw and is expected to take running down. Same goes for IN HER STRIDE (1) who has a big weight but good early speed and a low draw. Veteran mare racing in top form with two wins win end before a solid placing in a tougher race at Cranbourne. Freshened since and has won only try here. Take catching. LOOSE ON GIN (5) was safely held fresh on soft ground then improved sharply second-up to finish in the minors. Is a third-up winner and worth following up. SHEANADH (13) has the blinkers added and in this easier company, is worth another chance.
